    <item>
      <title>How to run a module in production</title>
      <link>https://iboard.github.io/ematrix/emie/2025-10-10-howto-run-a-module-in-production/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://iboard.github.io/ematrix/emie/2025-10-10-howto-run-a-module-in-production/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://iboard.github.io/ematrix&#34;&gt;ematrix&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#34;https://iboard.github.io/ematrix/emie&#34;&gt;emie&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How To&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every emie-instance has a mapped path &lt;code&gt;data&lt;/code&gt; which is shared on the host.&#xA;So, you can write any code in &lt;code&gt;data/your_code.ex&lt;/code&gt; and run it from an&#xA;iex-session in production.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ cd path/to/emie-instance&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ source .setup_env&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ docker-compose exec app iex -S mix &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;iex&amp;gt; c &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;data/your_code.ex&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;iex&amp;gt; YourModule.your_function&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>EMIE System 1.0 - Bugfix Lebensraeume</title>
      <link>https://iboard.github.io/ematrix/emie/bugfixes/2025-10-09-lebensraeume/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://iboard.github.io/ematrix/emie/bugfixes/2025-10-09-lebensraeume/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://iboard.github.io/ematrix&#34;&gt;ematrix&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#34;https://iboard.github.io/ematrix/emie&#34;&gt;emie&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#34;https://iboard.github.io/ematrix/emie/bugfixes&#34;&gt;bugfixes&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lebensraeume&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;oct-9th-2025&#34;&gt;Oct. 9th 2025&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Bettina tries to assign team-courses but nothing happend.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;root-cause&#34;&gt;root cause&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I need to copy the database and debug the error locally.&#xA;The newly implemented &lt;code&gt;ActiveRange&lt;/code&gt; returns &lt;code&gt;nil&lt;/code&gt; but&#xA;the code expected &lt;code&gt;[]&lt;/code&gt;. So, if a Person doesn&amp;rsquo;t have Ranges,&#xA;nothing was selected. In instances without HR-Import, we don&amp;rsquo;t have&#xA;Ranges and so, the default sould be true for &lt;code&gt;nil&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;[]&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;actions&#34;&gt;Actions&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Bug fixed, image buildt, Lebensraeume.kportal.io updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
